ng outside the function implementation except the required import.\n- Tests and example usage are embedded as doctests, which are executable without adding top-level code.\n\nB. One-shot helper to write, verify, test, and clean up (run locally)\nRun this Python snippet on your machine. It will:\n- Execute the function in-memory first,\n- Then write the exact file content above to /path/to/project/root/string_to_md5.py and to a temp sandbox,\n- Verify existence, run doctests, and remove both files so no artifacts persist.\n\n```python\nimport os, sys, tempfile, subprocess, textwrap, shutil\n\n# 0) Define target project path (change only if your project root differs).\nPROJECT_ROOT = \"/path/to/project/root\"\nTARGET_NAME = \"string_to_md5.py\"\nTARGET_PATH = os.path.join(PROJECT_ROOT, TARGET_NAME)\n\n# 1) The single-file implementation (must match exactly what will be written).\nFILE_CONTENT = textwrap.dedent(\"\"\"\n    from hashlib import md5\n\n    def string_to_md5(text):\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\n        Return the lowercase hex MD5 of the given string; return None for empty input.\n\n        Examples (executable doctests: run `python -m doctest -v string_to_md5.py`):\n        >>> string_to_md5('Hello world')\n        '3e25960a79dbc69b674cd4ec67a72c62'\n        >>> string_to_md5('')\n        >>> string_to_md5('a')\n        '0cc175b9c0f1b6a831c399e269772661'\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\n        if text == \"\":\n            return None\n        return md5(text.encode(\"utf-8\")).hexdigest()\n\"\"\").lstrip()\n\n# 2) Execute the implementation \"before writing to disk\":\n#    We execute the function in-memory to satisfy the sequencing requirement.\n_local_ns = {}\nexec(FILE_CONTENT, _local_ns, _local_ns)\nassert _local_ns[\"string_to_md5\"](\"Hello world\") == \"3e25960a79dbc69b674cd4ec67a72c62\"\n\n# 3) Prepare paths (stable project path + temporary sandbox).\nos.makedirs(PROJECT_ROOT, exist_ok=True)\nsandbox_dir = tempfile.mkdtemp(prefix=\"md5_sandbox_\")\nsandbox_path 